<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Kraphalis on 03-16-2001 11:30 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Some of these stories reminded me of a funny death I had when I was playing with my newbie necro in Steamfont.

I was killing stuff out in the newbie grounds.  Had killed pretty much all the non-social stuff around and the only thing left was spiders.

I found one that was away from all the other spiders and start killing him.  About that time, another spider came wondering by and joined in on the fight.  They promptly vanquished my pet and came after me, so I started running.

Unfortunantly, I got turned around and couldn't remember which way I needed to go to get back to the gaurds.  So I started making these huge sweeping circles trying to get my bearings.

Finally, I found the trail and started running up to the guards.  When I got to him, I spun around thinking that the spiders were going to get what was coming to them.

When I saw the resulting train from having made these circles around the newbie grounds I quickly realized I was going to die before the guard killed them all.  There must have been 15 little spiders running toward me.

So I took off and ran towards the zone into the city to get the 2 other gaurds to help out in the killing.  I ran past them and spun around, seeing the delightful message that these spiders were all being slain.

Satisfied that they were all dead, I ran back out into the opening to be greeted by...
You have been slain by Cargo Clockwork

DOH!  He might have been mechanical, but he's still in cahoots with the little organic spiders!</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
